-You got a boyfriend, Sam?

140
00:07:14,702 --> 00:07:16,637
No.

141
00:07:16,671 --> 00:07:18,539
You fucking anybody?

142
00:07:18,572 --> 00:07:19,774
[ Scoffs ]

143
00:07:19,807 --> 00:07:20,908
Stop.

144
00:07:20,942 --> 00:07:22,243
Gross.

145
00:07:22,276 --> 00:07:23,878
[ Laughs ]

146
00:07:23,911 --> 00:07:26,681
She's not your type, Billy.
She's still a kid.

147
00:07:29,016 --> 00:07:31,419
Look at how she dresses.

148
00:07:34,255 --> 00:07:37,224
Sam's way cooler than you,
you troglodytes.

149
00:07:38,626 --> 00:07:39,994
What's a troglodyte?

150
00:07:40,962 --> 00:07:42,530
Oh, it's like a --
like a caveman.

151
00:07:42,563 --> 00:07:45,599
It's calling them, like,
underdeveloped, stupid.

152
00:07:45,633 --> 00:07:47,902
-That's you guys.
-Why the fuck are we still here?

153
00:07:47,935 --> 00:07:49,971
This shit is lame.
Let's dip.

154
00:07:51,706 --> 00:07:54,075
GARY:
Yeah, run away.

155
00:07:54,108 --> 00:07:55,910
I hope to see you around,
Sam.

156
00:08:01,882 --> 00:08:04,218
They're lucky I didn't leave
them in a pile of blood.

157
00:08:04,251 --> 00:08:06,053
Yeah, those guys
are assholes.

158
00:08:06,087 --> 00:08:08,055
Yeah,
they weren't very nice.

159
00:08:08,089 --> 00:08:11,592
GARY: Come on, Jack.
Say something meaner.

160
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:13,561
JACK:
They were dumb.

161
00:08:13,594 --> 00:08:17,064
BROADCASTER: <i>Divers are still</i>
<i>searching for three fishermen</i>

162
00:08:17,098 --> 00:08:20,034
<i>whose boat was found adrift</i>
<i>earlier this week.</i>

163
00:08:20,067 --> 00:08:23,237
<i>Many people reported</i>
<i>seeing a fiery object</i>

164
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:26,040
<i>fall from the sky</i>
<i>that same evening.</i>

165
00:08:26,073 --> 00:08:28,709
<i>It is unknown</i>
<i>if the two events are related,</i>

166
00:08:28,743 --> 00:08:33,114
<i>but police are asking for</i>
<i>any witnesses to come forward.</i>

167
00:08:33,147 --> 00:08:37,685
<i>In other news, Halloween</i>
<i>is only two days away.</i>

168
00:08:37,718 --> 00:08:40,254
<i>Do you know what costume</i>
<i>you'll be wearing?</i>

169
00:08:40,287 --> 00:08:43,858
<i>Coming up,</i>
<i>we've got some great ideas.</i>

170
00:08:43,891 --> 00:08:46,093
[ Cellphone chimes ]

171
00:08:58,973 --> 00:09:00,341
[ Knock on door ]

172
00:09:00,374 --> 00:09:02,877
GARY: Sam, why do you always
lock your door?

173
00:09:03,944 --> 00:09:05,212
Sam, I know you're in there.

174
00:09:05,246 --> 00:09:07,014
Are you coming out to wrestle
or not?

175
00:09:07,048 --> 00:09:09,016
Not right now.

176
00:09:10,651 --> 00:09:13,621
What?
Come on. Why not?

177
00:09:13,654 --> 00:09:15,222
We need you.

178
00:09:15,256 --> 00:09:17,925
Because I don't
feel like it.

179
00:09:17,958 --> 00:09:20,127
Come on.

180
00:09:20,161 --> 00:09:22,897
We need you
for this movie.

181
00:09:22,930 --> 00:09:25,766
I thought you were gonna be
my tag-team partner.

182
00:09:28,169 --> 00:09:30,004
Come on.

183
00:09:31,105 --> 00:09:32,339
Why not?

184
00:09:32,373 --> 00:09:33,974
Gary, I have homework.

185
00:09:34,008 --> 00:09:35,276
[ Cellphone chimes ]

186
00:09:39,780 --> 00:09:41,715
[ <i>Playing mid-tempo music</i> ]

187
00:09:44,785 --> 00:09:46,287
Just shoot it without me.

188
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:49,156
And don't do anything
that'll get me in trouble.

189
00:09:49,190 --> 00:09:52,226
Fine.
Be like that!

190
00:09:52,793 --> 00:09:57,198
♪ <i>You wanted me,</i>
<i>and I didn't see it</i> ♪

191
00:09:59,667 --> 00:10:04,071
♪ <i>Now I'm so lost without you</i> ♪

192
00:10:14,915 --> 00:10:16,250
Get off me, dummy!

193
00:10:16,283 --> 00:10:18,652
GARY: Nice.

194
00:10:18,686 --> 00:10:20,121
Where's Sam?

195
00:10:20,154 --> 00:10:23,090
Uh, she needed
to do homework.

196
00:10:23,124 --> 00:10:24,658
What the fuck?

197
00:10:24,692 --> 00:10:26,127
Why would she want a main role
in the movie

198
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:27,761
if she's not gonna be in it?

199
00:10:27,795 --> 00:10:29,296
Yeah, I know.
I thought the exact same thing.

200
00:10:29,330 --> 00:10:31,932
It's kind of weird.
She's never ditched us before.

201
00:10:31,966 --> 00:10:34,902
Jack, here are the glow sticks
you wanted.

202
00:10:34,935 --> 00:10:36,837
Sweet. Thanks.

203
00:10:36,871 --> 00:10:38,906
What are you even doing?

204
00:10:38,939 --> 00:10:40,341
I already told you.

205
00:10:40,374 --> 00:10:42,143
I'm working on the grand finale
for the movie,

206
00:10:42,176 --> 00:10:44,445
and it's going to be glorious.

207
00:10:44,478 --> 00:10:46,080
Sure.

208
00:10:46,113 --> 00:10:50,384
Yeah, just, um, don't blow
anything up, please.

209
00:10:50,417 --> 00:10:53,120
No promises.

210
00:10:53,154 --> 00:10:55,156
Wait.

211
00:10:55,189 --> 00:10:57,992
So she totally ditched us
for homework.

212
00:10:58,025 --> 00:10:59,960
Yeah.
Well, guess what.

213
00:10:59,994 --> 00:11:02,429
Sucks to be her
because she won't get to film

214
00:11:02,463 --> 00:11:04,999
the best movie ever.

215
00:11:05,032 --> 00:11:07,101
Let's film this fucking thing.

216
00:11:07,134 --> 00:11:11,005
It's pandemonium here
as one half of the Berserkers

217
00:11:11,038 --> 00:11:14,241
faces off against
the treacherous Dino Sorcerer.

218
00:11:14,275 --> 00:11:18,212
A match that's been
65 million years in the making.

219
00:11:18,245 --> 00:11:21,081
-Now let's rumble!
-[ Bell dings ]

220
00:11:21,115 --> 00:11:24,018
DINO:
My kind was frozen in the dirt

221
00:11:24,051 --> 00:11:27,454
until the souls of your
ancestors brought us back!

222
00:11:29,823 --> 00:11:31,425
I can't believe it!

223
00:11:31,458 --> 00:11:33,727
The Dino Sorcerer has brought
the Berserker to his knees.

224
00:11:33,761 --> 00:11:35,429
[ Roars ]

225
00:11:37,164 --> 00:11:38,499
[ Grunting ]

226
00:11:38,533 --> 00:11:40,367
Holy smokes, folks!

227
00:11:40,401 --> 00:11:42,870
We're watching history
rewrite itself.

228
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:48,409
Just because my tag-team partner
isn't willing to help me

229
00:11:48,442 --> 00:11:49,877
because they have homework,

230
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:51,378
that doesn't mean
that I'm not ready

231
00:11:51,412 --> 00:11:54,748
to fight anything and anyone
in this shithole universe

232
00:11:54,782 --> 00:11:56,750
to protect my Planet Earth.

233
00:11:56,784 --> 00:11:57,885
[ Roars ]

234
00:12:00,087 --> 00:12:01,855
The Dino Sorcerer is hurt.

235
00:12:01,889 --> 00:12:04,391
The fate of the planet
comes down to this very moment.

236
00:12:04,425 --> 00:12:05,960
I'm unstoppable!

237
00:12:05,993 --> 00:12:08,162
Oh, fuck!

238
00:12:08,195 --> 00:12:09,997
[ Groaning ]

239
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:11,432
My arm!
I broke it!

240
00:12:11,465 --> 00:12:12,499
Go get my sister!
Go, go!

241
00:12:12,534 --> 00:12:14,168
Jack, go!

242
00:12:14,201 --> 00:12:15,836
Don't be a wuss, man.

243
00:12:15,869 --> 00:12:18,305
You don't be a fucking dumbass!
Get off my arm!

244
00:12:18,339 --> 00:12:21,075
-[ Shrieking ]
-It's not my fault!

245
00:12:22,176 --> 00:12:25,312
Fuck, fuck, fuck!
Mom and Dad are gonna piss!

246
00:12:25,346 --> 00:12:26,947
I just broke my arm.

247
00:12:26,981 --> 00:12:29,283
Can you stop yelling at me
for fucking second?

248
00:12:29,316 --> 00:12:30,818
SAM:
I didn't want to bike

249
00:12:30,851 --> 00:12:32,820
to the fucking hospital today,
you moron!

250
00:12:32,853 --> 00:12:35,923
GARY: Too fucking bad!
I broke my arm!

251
00:12:37,258 --> 00:12:40,394
God.
Sam, this looks so cool!

252
00:12:40,427 --> 00:12:42,997
It's like glow-in-the-dark
and everything.

253
00:12:44,465 --> 00:12:46,000
Why do you look like that?

254
00:12:47,067 --> 00:12:48,168
Like what?

255
00:12:48,202 --> 00:12:50,771
Like that.
It looks stupid.

256
00:12:51,438 --> 00:12:53,874
Gary, you fell off a ladder.

257
00:12:53,907 --> 00:12:56,511
At least I was doing something
for the movie.

258
00:12:56,544 --> 00:12:58,379
You really picked
an inconvenient time

259
00:12:58,412 --> 00:13:00,281
